theorem Reverse Disjunction
premise ∨ φ ψ
assume φ {
  prove ∨ ψ φ
}
prove → φ ∨ ψ φ
assume ψ {
  prove ∨ ψ φ
}
prove → ψ ∨ ψ φ
prove ∨ ψ φ
qed

theorem One Disjunct Must Be True
premise ∨ φ ψ
premise ¬ φ
prove → ¬ φ ψ
prove ψ
qed

theorem One Disjunct Must Be True
