theorem Disjunction of Two Falsehoods Is False
premise ¬ φ
premise ¬ ψ
assume φ {
  prove ¬ ∨ φ ψ
}
assume ψ {
  prove ¬ ∨ φ ψ
}
assume ∨ φ ψ {
  prove ¬ ∨ φ ψ
}
prove ¬ ∨ φ ψ
qed

theorem Proof by Cases
premise proves φ ψ
premise proves ¬ φ χ
assume φ {
  prove ψ
  prove ∨ ψ χ
}
assume ¬ φ {
  prove χ
  prove ∨ ψ χ
}
prove ∨ ψ χ
qed

theorem Law of the Excluded Middle
prove → ¬ φ ¬ φ
prove ∨ φ ¬ φ
qed

theorem Eliminate Redundant Or
premise ∨ φ ψ
premise proves φ ψ
assume ψ {
  prove ψ
}
prove ψ
qed
